  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - ENCHANTER</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>PLAYS WELL WITH OTHERS</font> - <small>Faumelnox, Erollisi Marr</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>In my travels I have noticed a high number of enchanters sitting by themselves, in a safe place, meditating while their pet runs in circles around them.  I am going to point out what everyone already knows, one more time:  Our pets are dangerous to us.  It is much better to have other players watch your back while medding, they can attack any aggressors BEFORE they get to you.  Staring at the book is BORING, it is less so when you are chattering up a storm with other players.
<P>
I have also noticed that many enchanters don't know what to do when they get in a group.  More often then not, they buff when they should be blasting, or blast when they should be buff/debuffing.  I have seen many groups get killed because they were counting on the enchanter to stop a critter, and the enchanter was the first one to drop.  So I have put together a rather compressed list of things to do when in a group.  Remember, your best friends will always be the people you buff...
<P>
[Disclaimer:  It is assumed that you are involved in single pulls.  But multiple pulls work about the same way.]
<P>

<U>Cleric/Druid/Shaman/Paladin/Bard:</U>  Finally, someone that can take a beating and keep you alive.  Always nice to have around.  Buff them the same as Warrior types, if you have the mana.  They can buff themselves pretty good, but a Quickness never hurt anyone.  Remember to give them some breathing room to heal themselves [and you] up with a Languid Pace, or a Whirl.
<P>
[Average fight:  20-30 seconds, 6-7 casts]
<P>
<U>Enchanter/Wizard/Necromancer/Magician:</U>  Think pinball.  Position everyone [safely] about a spell distance apart.  Then just have fun blasting the critter, watch it aggro, and laugh at its confusion as it attempts to hit someone.  Done correctly, you will get hit once or twice.  Just remember to use high aggro spells like sanity warp, especially if you are with a wizard.  If someone is taking too many hits, give them a chance to cast with Whirl.  
<P>
[Average fight: 15 seconds, 3-4 casts]
<P>
<U>Monk/Ranger/Rouge/Shadow Knight/Warrior:</U>  Ah.  These types LOVE Enchanters.  If you need some quick XP just hook up with one 3-5 levels higher than you.  Your sole job is to make sure that they can kill whatever you're fighting quickly.  After snapping off a Quickness, just sink a few Tashani's into the creature they are pounding, then Languid Pace and Whirl to your hearts content.  They love that.  Remember to always cast Quickness BEFORE the fight starts, this is important to remember if you know the fight is going to have more than one beastie, since it will immeditely pull all the remaing nasties to you.
<P>
[Average fight:  really depends on how long you want it to last, prepare to blow all your mana and never have more than 30-40% until you disband]

</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
